## Step 1.3: Handle JSONB Properties (If Needed)

### When to Use JsonbProperty

If your entity has JSONB columns, wrap them with `JsonbProperty<T>`:

```typescript
import { JsonbProperty } from 'src/engine/workspace-manager/workspace-migration/universal-flat-entity/types/jsonb-property.type';

@Entity('myEntity')
export class MyEntityEntity extends SyncableEntity {
  // JSONB column - must wrap with JsonbProperty
  @Column({ type: 'jsonb', nullable: false })
  configuration: JsonbProperty<MyEntityConfiguration>;
}
```

### When to Use SerializedRelation

If JSONB properties contain foreign key IDs, use `SerializedRelation`:

```typescript
import { SerializedRelation } from 'twenty-shared/types';

type MyEntityConfiguration = {
  name: string;
  // Foreign key in JSONB - use SerializedRelation
  targetFieldMetadataId: SerializedRelation;
  // Regular property
  displayFormat: string;
};
```

**Result:** In universal entities, `targetFieldMetadataId` becomes `targetFieldMetadataUniversalIdentifier`

